ack rubber band is in play. NEVER chase highs; wait for the pullback.</p><h=
3>Key TA Tools I Use (Simple Version)</h3><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0=
">Support &amp; Resistance: Floors (support) where prices often bounce, cei=
lings (resistance) where they stall. Tip Watch if Nasdaq/Q's hold support o=
r break down.</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Moving Averages (e.g.,=
 200-day): Key "fair value" lines. Price above =3D bullish trend; below =3D=
 caution. Hitting the 200-day (like AVGO) is often a solid buy zone.</p></l=
i><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">ATR Levels: Measures volatility. Minus 2, =
